=================================================================
F. QUANTITATIVE BIAS ANALYSIS
=================================================================
  2.6-3.0 subband OR loaded from CSV: 0.551
  Assumptions:
    U = complex surgery (long CPB / cross-clamp)
    OR_UY = effect of complex surgery on AKI
    p0 = P(complex | untreated), p1 = p0 - delta
    Bias factor = (OR_UY*p1 + 1-p1) / (OR_UY*p0 + 1-p0)
    Adjusted OR = Observed OR / Bias factor

  ── AC primary (eICU) (observed OR = 0.796) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.824 → adjusted OR=0.967 (still protective)
  ── IPTW (eICU) (observed OR = 0.869) ──
    Survives 30/36 scenarios (83%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.824 → adjusted OR=1.055 (CROSSES NULL)
  ── Mg >2.3 OW (eICU) (observed OR = 0.528) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.912 → adjusted OR=0.579 (still protective)
  ── Mg >2.3 AC (eICU) (observed OR = 0.549) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.912 → adjusted OR=0.602 (still protective)
  ── 2.6-3.0 subband (observed OR = 0.551) ──
    Survives 36/36 scenarios (100%)
    Worst case: bias factor=0.912 → adjusted OR=0.604 (still protective)

-----------------------------------------------------------------
QBA SUMMARY: Does the estimate survive?
-----------------------------------------------------------------
  Scenario: OR_UY=2.0, p0=0.40, delta=0.10 (moderate assumptions)
  For stratified estimates, delta halved to 0.05

  AC primary (eICU)         OR 0.796 → 0.857 ✓ survives
  IPTW (eICU)               OR 0.869 → 0.936 ✓ survives
  Mg >2.3 OW (eICU)         OR 0.528 → 0.548 ✓ survives
  Mg >2.3 AC (eICU)         OR 0.549 → 0.569 ✓ survives
  2.6-3.0 subband           OR 0.551 → 0.571 ✓ survives

  Key insight: within the >2.3 stratum, complexity is held
  approximately constant by stratification, so the prevalence
  difference shrinks → bias factor approaches 1 → adjusted
  estimate stays protective.

